<subSubSection id="E9C665140762FFF910130479FAEAA8CE" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph id="A163369F0762FFF910130479FC25A9AE" blockId="26.[811,1457,1651,1804]" box="[813,957,1651,1677]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F0762FFF910130498FC66A989" blockId="26.[811,1457,1651,1804]" box="[813,1022,1682,1708]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0762FFF910130498FC66A989" box="[813,1022,1682,1708]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Thoracic appendages</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F0762FFF9101304B8FA86A829" blockId="26.[811,1457,1651,1804]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Chelate P1; P1 propodus subrectangular; wide P1 fingers, straight, equal in length, as long as propodus; P1 carpus short, subtriangular; P1 merus short, subrectangular.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F0762FFF910130538FC57A869" blockId="26.[813,975,1842,1868]" box="[813,975,1842,1868]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">
<heading id="FA2B81F30762FFF910130538FC57A869" box="[813,975,1842,1868]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" reason="8">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0762FFF910130538FC57A869" box="[813,975,1842,1868]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Ornamentation</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F0762FFF910130558FAEAA8CE" blockId="26.[811,1457,1873,2028]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">P1 propodus covered by small tubercles; inner margin with a row of strong spines directed forward; fingers without ornamentation; P1 carpus covered by small tubercles and with strong spines directed forward on inner margin; P1 merus with strong spines directed forward on dorsal margin.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9C665140763FFF813BA02F2FD9EAD15" pageId="27" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A163369F0763FFF813BA02F2FE9EAE35" blockId="27.[132,777,248,561]" box="[132,262,248,274]" pageId="27" pageNumber="50">DISCUSSION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F0763FFF813BA031DFEF7AEB4" blockId="27.[132,777,248,561]" pageId="27" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0763FFF813BA031DFE05AE14" authorityName="Schweigert &amp; Roper" authorityYear="2001" box="[132,413,279,305]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Palaeastacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rothgaengerae">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0763FFF813BA031DFE05AE14" box="[132,413,279,305]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="50">Palaeastacus rothgaengerae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known by a very few isolated P1 with chelae characteristic of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0763FFF812E0033DFDC4AE74" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1850" box="[478,604,311,337]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Palaeastacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0763FFF812E0033DFDC4AE74" box="[478,604,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="50">Palaeastacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: short and subrectangular propodus, short and wide fingers, and strongly spiny ornamentation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F0763FFF813A5039DFD9EAD15" blockId="27.[132,777,248,561]" pageId="27" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0763FFF813A5039DFED8AE95" authorityName="Schweigert &amp; Roper" authorityYear="2001" box="[155,320,406,432]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Palaeastacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rothgaengerae">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0763FFF813A5039DFED8AE95" box="[155,320,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="50">P. rothgaengerae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly distinct among the other species of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0763FFF8139C03BCFEB8AEF5" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1850" box="[162,288,438,464]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Palaeastacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0763FFF8139C03BCFEB8AEF5" box="[162,288,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="50">Palaeastacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the particular shape of P1 fingers, which gives its characteristic appearance to the chelae. Indeed, the fingers are very wide with strongly rounded inner margin of dactylus and outer margin of index.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
